34
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,520
Obviously,

35
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:46,160
the attacker thrust upward.

36
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,200
So the assailant must be

37
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,640
much shorter than the victim.

38
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,000
Moreover,

39
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:54,400
there might be another possibility.

40
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,600
Perhaps the assailant was

41
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,760
crouching or sitting on the ground.

42
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,600
Mr. Qian was killed with a single stab.

43
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,440
The knife wound patterns are neat.

44
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,320
No property loss was found.

45
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,920
We do not rule out

46
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,760
he may have known the murderer.

47
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,200
The victim's skin is grayish-white,

48
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,280
swelling in the belly area.

49
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,440
Strange, why would it be this color?

50
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,560
Be careful.

51
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,480
Get down.

52
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,840
Do you think

53
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:53,640
the charred blanket
in front of the evil god statue

54
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,760
is the same as this one?

55
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,680
Actually, there was a person inside

56
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,600
It seems evil god

57
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,480
doesn't want us to know too much.

58
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:14,120
Some traces can't be completely hidden.

59
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,279
- Bao Long.
- Yes.

60
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,440
Go out and bring help.

61
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:19,320
Yes, sir.

62
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,320
It seems someone else should be here.

63
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,520
This person is the key to the case.

64
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,320
Ensure timely medication.

65
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,480
The symptoms should improve.

66
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,320
Thank you, Dr. Chu.

67
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:53,640
Mr. Chu,
why did Qin Yang's illness worsen?

68
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,520
The side effects of scopolamine

69
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,880
came sooner than I expected.

70
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,560
This medicine can't be used anymore.

71
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,080
Don't listen to him.

72
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,640
The medicine brings me comfort.

73
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,800
Otherwise, when it rains,

74
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,920
I feel worse than death.

75
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:15,880
What Mr. Chu said

76
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,240
you have a mental illness?

77
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,040
What's this all about?

78
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,600
Why are you afraid of the rain?

79
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,320
That's all in the past.

80
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,560
Let's skip that.

81
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,440
What is that?

82
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,880
This is from that assistant just now.

83
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,440
The medicine is bitter,

84
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:34,520
so he left me this.

85
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,240
And I am leaving it for you.

86
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,560
I understand.

87
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,600
I know why Mr. Qian self-ignited.

88
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,680
The black powder we saw in the morgue

89
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,360
is actually burnt sugar.

90
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,280
How could there be sugar there?

91
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,920
Potassium chlorate.

92
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:02,960
It is tasteless.

93
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,600
But it emits a pungent odor
when it decomposes.

94
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,160
That's what we smelled in the morgue.

95
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,600
Sugar and potassium chlorate
can ignite upon contact.

96
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:10,960
Everyone, step back.

97
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,320
What is this?

98
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,680
It actually has such power.

99
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,680
Far more effective than lime powder.

100
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,720
If I could carry some in my bag...

101
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,120
Be careful.

102
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,720
It is intrinsically unstable.

103
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,120
Before you tossed it,

104
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,080
it might've lit already.

105
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,040
Potassium chlorate,

106
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,640
can ordinary people get it?

107
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,800
Latest news,

108
